President Biden visited the U.K. at the invitation of the Prime Minister and in preparation for the G7 Summit. During the visit, the President and the Prime Minister established a new Atlantic Charter, outlining their shared global vision. The charter emphasized the importance of cooperation in democracy, human rights, defense, security, science, innovation, and economic prosperity. They also pledged to work together to address challenges related to climate change, biodiversity loss, and emerging health threats. The leaders also expressed their commitment to Northern Ireland.